m><span class=title> Character Design....</span><hr size=1> WEll, I'm sure we've all gots tons of characters running around shooting, slicing, and just whipping ass in our heads.  Then when it comes down to putting them down on the good ol' paper we get stuck.  I know I don't always have a general overview of my characters at first.  Honestly I've never actually had a full, all around concept pic of any of my characters.  The question is, what steps does everyone out there take to detailing their characters?  Examples would be great! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/usofianime.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sofianime</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pre-Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(5/23/01 5:51:39 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www16.brinkster.com/sofianime/lilicon3b.jpg height=100 width=100></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Character Design....</span><hr size=1> I usually start by writing down a description of what my character looks like and anything else tyhat makes your character be unique.<br>
Then I create a model sheet of the character, based on the written description. I would do a front, side, back and 3/4 view of the character. I would also do a model sheet of the weapons the character uses. I also create a color version of the model sheet, so you know what color the character should be.<br>
It also helps to do as many facial gestures as you can of your character, so you have an idea of what his/her emotions will be like.<br>
Hope that helps ya!<br>
Sofi! :P <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ulordgabriel3.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lord Gabriel 3</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(5/23/01 5:53:02 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Character Design....</span><hr size=1> well, my site really sucks, but here's a tutorial I made that explains how to develop characters (very simplistically)<br>
